issue.title: FIX: Virtual Network Resource Group dependency
issue.body: # Overview/summary This pull request fixes the issue where terraform was throwing a 404 error ResourceGroupNotFound when trying to deploy a route table or network security group into the virtual network resource group. By moving the resource_group_data logic out of the virtual network module and moving it to be used against the resource group module allows the network resource group to be created before any network resources if set to enabled. ## This PR fixes/adds/changes/removes 1. fixes #473 ### Breaking changes 1. Existing deployments may try to replace the resources if they are ran again due to the Network resource group being created in a new module. ## Testing evidence Please provide testing evidence to show that your Pull Request works/fixes as described and documented above. This has been tested locally based on several scenarios: - resource_group_creation_enabled and resource_group_creation_enabled within the virtual network variable both set to false - resource_group_creation_enabled set to false and resource_group_creation_enabled within the virtual network variable set to true - resource_group_creation_enabled set to true and resource_group_creation_enabled within the virtual network variable set to false Below is a screenshot of the resources deployed into the same resource group ## As part of this pull request I have - [x] Checked for duplicate [Pull Requests](https://github.com/Azure/terraform-azurerm-lz-vending/pulls) - [x] Associated it with relevant [issues](https://github.com/Azure/terraform-azurerm-lz-vending/issues), for tracking and closure. - [x] Run and `make fmt` & `make docs` to format your code and update documentation. - [x] Created unit and deployment tests and provided evidence. - [x] Updated relevant and associated documentation.

pull_request.title: chore: downgrade to libc@0.2.174
pull_request.body:
### What does this PR try to resolve?

There is incompatibility between rustix@1.0.8 and libc@0.2.175 that leads to compilation errors.

See

* https://github.com/bytecodealliance/rustix/issues/1496
* https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/145478#issuecomment-3193494156

### How to test and review this PR?

In rust-lang/rust, update the `src/tools/cargo` submodule accordingly, and run

```
cargo run --manifest-path src/ci/citool/Cargo.toml run-local dist-loongarch64-musl
```

With this downgrade it should compile.

pull_request.title: [testing] Really run dotnetutils tests
pull_request.body:
Related: #2158 

dotnetutils.test.js wasn't added to package.json, so it wasn't actually running. I was running unit tests from the IDE and assumed everything was working. Unfortunately, one of the unit tests was referring to the incorrect property `packageName` instead of `name`, so it was broken. Fortunately, the function in utils.js was referring to the correct property, so the end users aren't affected.

Why didn't biome catch this? Because we [disabled](https://github.com/CycloneDX/cdxgen/blob/42c3c6c173096f085fe29c5bd589658b820d8df6/biome.json#L29) linting for unit tests. That's why you should use TypeScript or Rust, did you say? Yes, I agree.

Also updated packages.

pull_request.title: Add opt-in ‚ÄúRight-click to pan‚Äù; `m` opens context menu
pull_request.body:
This PR introduces an optional mode that enables Miro-style panning with the right mouse button.

Behavior
- When the option **Pan with right mouse button** is ON:
  - Right-click + drag pans the canvas.
  - The native context menu is suppressed during the drag.
  - Pressing `m` opens the context menu (only when not editing text).

- When the option is OFF:
  - No change to current behavior.

Scope
- Desktop mouse only; touch/stylus unaffected.
- Default: OFF.
- No breaking changes.

API surface
- Adds an opt-in flag exposed to host apps to toggle this behavior (wireable by host/plugin settings).

Implementation notes
- Right-button (secondary) pointer down initiates temporary pan via existing pan logic.
- A one-shot `contextmenu` preventDefault is used to avoid native menu during pan.
- Guarded to avoid triggering while editing text.

Testing
- Verify:
  - With the flag OFF: right-click still opens native context menu as today.
  - With the flag ON: right-click + drag pans; `m` opens context menu when not in text edit.
  - No changes to touch/stylus interactions.
